= Some Properties of the Euler Equations
== The One-Dimensional Euler Equations
=== Conservative Formulation

$
U_t + F(U)_x = 0
$
where,
$
U = vec(rho, rho u, E) &"conserved variables"\
F = vec(rho u, rho u^2 + p, u(E+p)) &"Flux"\
E=rho(1/2 u^2 + e) &"total energy"\ 
e=e(rho,p) = p/((gamma - 1) rho) &"specific internal energy"\
gamma = c_p/c_v &"ratio of specific heats"\
a = sqrt((gamma p)/rho)
$

This can also be written, 

$
U_t + A(U)U_x = 0
$







